\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. A. calabra} (Fiori) Ehrend. & Krendl, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  68}: 268 (1974) ({\i A. cynanchica} var.{\i  calabra} Fiori). Like {\b 4} but shoots glaucous or green; stems 10-25(-30) cm, more caespitose, only slightly woody at base; leaves 7-15 × 1-2 mm, narrowly oblanceolate, brownish to blackish when dry, rather thin, acute; margin weakly revolute; corolla 7-12 mm, pale purplish, glabrous outside or rarely more or less patent-hairy; fruit glabrous. •{\i  Mountains of S.W. Italy.} It.
