\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. A. staliana} Vis.,{\i  Fl. Dalm.}{\b  3}: 11 (1852). Shoots always glaucous-pruinose, laxly caespitose. Stems 10-35 cm, ascending, more or less woody and glabrous or shortly hairy at the base; middle internodes 1-2 times as long as the leaves. Leaves 10-30 × 1*5-3*5 mm, thickish, acute, in pairs on upper two-thirds of stem; midrib comprising less than 3/4 of width of leaf; margin revolute. Inflorescence ovoid, moderately dense; partial inflorescences condensed to more or less capitate. Corolla 3-8 mm, hypocrateriform to narrowly infundibuliform, pink, glabrous outside; tube 2-3 times as long as the distinctly appendiculate lobes. Fruit c. 2 mm, papillose, otherwise glabrous, glaucous-pruinose.{\i  Maritime rocks. • Islands off the coast of N.W. Jugoslavia.} Ju.
