\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. A. ophiolithica} Ehrend., {\i Pl. Syst. Evol.}{\b  123}: 153 (1975) ({\i A. stricta} auct. eur., non Boiss.,{\i  A. stricta} subsp.{\i  pruinosa} Ehrend.). Shoots glaucous-pruinose, particularly when young. Stems 20-45 cm, woody at base, ascending, glabrous or with patent hairs up to 0*3 mm below. Leaves 8-15 × 0*5-0*8 mm, linear, usually straight and erect; midrib comprising more than 3/4 of width of leaf; margin revolute. Inflorescence elongate, somewhat branched, laxly spicate, with 4-6 flower-clusters; bracts scarcely connate. Corolla 4·2-5·2 mm, hypocrateriform, brownish-yellow, more or less glabrous; tube 2-3 times as long as lobes. Fruit 2-3 mm, papillose. {\i Serpentine rocks. • E. Greece} ({\i Evvoia}). Gr.
